===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally written {{zh-l|譱}} in {{w|bronze inscriptions}}, consisting of two {{och-l|言}} and one {{zh-l|*羊}}. The {{och-l|言}} might have served as the phonetic component, while {{zh-l|*羊}} represented the sense "good; beautiful" (see {{zh-l|*祥}}, {{zh-l|*義}}). The small seal script of {{lang|zh|善}} was simplified from the bronze inscription form, consisting of one {{zh-l|*言}} below one {{zh-l|*羊}}.

According to ''{{w|Shuowen}}'', the form
{{zh-l|譱}} is an {{Han compound|誩|羊|ls=ic|t1=to wrangle|t2=sheep|nocap=1}} – good; virtuous. This interpretation may be difficult to comprehend.

===Etymology===
Probably related to {{och-l|繕|gloss=to mend; to repair}}.

